Add structured logging via tracing

Minimalist mapping of the sdh-fleet-client logging stack to this
workspace. Two layers (compact console on stderr, JSON daily-
rolling on disk) share a single EnvFilter that defaults to INFO
and honours RUST_LOG for overrides.

The log directory follows the same three-level resolution as
sdh-fleet-client/src/logging.rs:

1. RUST_POC_LOG_DIR env var, if set (operator escape hatch).
2. <exe-dir>/logs/ — what production-style runs use.
3. ./logs/ relative to CWD as last resort.

Hot-reload is deliberately NOT ported. The fleet-client needs it
because fleet-config publishes new log levels at runtime; Rust-Poc
has no such source, so the extra reload::Layer + log_reload worker
would be unjustified complexity.

Crate-level wiring:

- root crate gains tracing + tracing-subscriber + tracing-appender
  and owns src/logging.rs and the WorkerGuard.
- greeter crate gains tracing (only) so its impls can emit debug!
  events. Without a subscriber installed (unit tests), the macros
  are no-ops, so test setup stays empty.
- contracts crate is left alone — pure data types should not log.

Call-site idioms documented in CLAUDE.md:

- info!(field = value, "msg") with structured fields, never
  interpolated into the message string.
- %expr for Display, ?expr for Debug.
- Operator instruction: set RUST_POC_LOG_DIR to C:\SMSLogs at the
  user level so log output goes to the team's standard location.

Validated locally:
- cargo fmt --all -- --check
- cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings
- cargo test --workspace (21 tests, all green)
- cargo run -p rust-poc (default dir: target/debug/logs/)
- $env:RUST_POC_LOG_DIR=...; $env:RUST_LOG=debug; cargo run
  (verified override + debug-level greeter events surface)
